  "body": "**ðŸ§ Motivation**\r\nKnowing what tokenIds an address owns is useful for iterating through NFTs that the address owns.\r\nThe amount per tokenId is not necessary since one could always call balanceOf()\r\n\r\n**ðŸ“ Details**\r\n// owner to ownedTokenIds[]\r\nmapping(address => uint256[]) tokenIdsByOwner\r\n\r\nThen pushing/removing to the array on transfer.\r\nThis will probably look the same as the ERC721Enumerable.\r\n\r\nI could make a pull request for it but I just wanted to know if there are any problems/issues with making an enumerable ERC1155 implementation?\r\n\r\n<!-- Make sure that you have reviewed the OpenZeppelin Contracts Contributor Guidelines. -->\r\n<!-- https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md -->\r\n",
