    "body": "Hello @SKFrozenCloud \r\n\r\nThis is quite easy to do, but would greatly increase the gas cost of operations. So I'd love to know more about your use-case and you need to have this information onchain.\r\n\r\nNote that is only needed to be on-chain if another contract is reading it. If what you want is building an explorer, then you don't need that to be stored on-chain (at great cost for the user) and can instead rely on something like [this subgraph](https://thegraph.com/explorer/subgraph?id=0x7859821024e633c5dc8a4fcf86fc52e7720ce525-1&view=Playground)\r\n\r\nIt allows you to do queries such as\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  account(id: \"0x000000000000000000000000000000000000dead\") {\r\n    ERC1155balances {\r\n      contract {\r\n        id\r\n      }\r\n      token {\r\n        identifier\r\n        uri\r\n      }\r\n      valueExact\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nYour package [@opezeppelin/subgraphs](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-subgraphs) contains everything you need to deploy a similar subgraph for any contract on any chain.",
